description: This story recounts the origins of Rakan, his uncanny association with the ebony saber-toothed cat and the reason for his unending quest for a girl.
name: Sabretooth

description: Rakan has become a player in a deadly chess match. Only it is not between chess pieces, but living men! Will Rakan survive the final check mate?
name: Chess Master

description: Rakan saves some travelers from a horde of demon bats, and is set forth on a quest for a legendary sword. Among the perils he faces is a beautiful and mysterious woman. Could she be the missing Reem?
name: The Sword of Majido

description: One of Wizard's first volumes exclusively honoring a well-known superhero. In this issue we get an in-depth multi-articled analysis of the Man of Steel and how he has developed over the years. His influence, enemies, powers and more are all taken into account in this issue that is simply a must for any fan of the Man of Tomorrow.
name: Superman Tribute Edition

description:
IT'S ALL BEEN BUILDING TO THE AVENGERS!

  • The Avengers is due for release 4th May 2012 and is set to be THE blockbuster of 2012!
  • Directed by Joss Whendon, The Avengers brings together the stars of Iron Man Robert Downey Jr), Thor (Chris Hemsworth ) and Captain America (Chris Evans) and also stars, Scarlett Johanson, Samuel L Jackson, Tom Hiddleston.
  • Includes an exclusive introduction by team co-creator and founder of the Marvel Universe, Stan Lee!
  • Includes the Avengers Marvel Universe entry, detailing his history and powers.
  • Includes the true origin of the Avengers, discussing how the creators came up with the team, who was to be included and how they evolved.
  • Not available as a US import (UK-specific book)
  • An essential guide to The Avengers!
  • Easily accessible to new readers.
name: Marvel Platinum: The Definitive Avengers
